    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Joy of Giving</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Donald Stewart letter welcomes news that charitable giving by Americans rose 9 percent in 1999 (May 25 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Charitable Giving Surged Again in '99, by an Estimated 9%'' (news article, May 25):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Charitable Giving Surged Again in '99, by an Estimated 9%'' (news article, May 25):</p>
        <p>It is positively heartening to know that American philanthropic endeavors have grown at such an incredible pace, outflanking the country's economic growth and continuing a tradition that has been apparent throughout our nation's history. In today's technological revolution, it is both joyous and remarkable to read that we still consider charitable endeavors a top priority.</p>
        <p>As early as 1835, Alexis de Tocqueville commented on the extraordinary commitment this country had to good works. A hundred and sixty-five years later, this sentiment continues to resound deeply in the hearts and actions of the American people.</p>
        <p>DONALD STEWART  New York, May 25, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
